  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: SecondDayConvo01
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: SecondDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Good evening, my pocket-sized peon. Another beautiful night to make me
      money, is it not?
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Your performance yesterday was surprisingly acceptable. Efficient, quiet,
      and with only a moderate amount of screaming. Very professional.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Listen up-- tonight\u2019s <b>quota</b> is <b>(Insert Quota Here)</b>.
      You <i>will</i> have to work hard to reach it, but it's important to remember
      to have a work-life balance..."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: If you don't <i>work</i>, you won't have a <i>life to balance</i>, heh
      heh!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Oh, yes-- and how has the <b>bone saw</b> been treating you? It can be
      tricky, but even a dim creature like you will get the hang of it eventually.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Tonight, I have a new tool to give you. Every new tool will open up an
      entirely new product line, which means <i>more money</i>-- so get used to using
      more tools.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "This one is <i>also</i> a <b>saw</b>-- but it is specifically for removing
      <b>arms</b> and <b>legs</b>. Let\u2019s hope customers pay and arm and a leg
      for them, heh heh!"
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
